    <text id="R13770475T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>In this May, 1864, dispatch, Union Assistant Adjutant D. C. Wager orders General
                    Franz Sigel to attack Staunton and destroy the railroad there in order to
                    disrupt Lee's flow of supplies.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>
        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    <name type="recipient"> Maj.-Gen. SIGEL, Strasburg, Va.:</name>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1864-05-17">May 17, 1864 </date><time>--10 p. m.</time>
                        <name type="place">WASHINGTON, D. C.,</name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute/>
                </opener>
                <p>Lieut.-Gen. Grant expects that you will go up the Shenandoah Valley to Staunton
                    and destroy the railroad there, so as to prevent Gen. Lee's drawing supplies
                    from there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute/>
                    <signed>D. C. WAGER,<lb/> Capt. and Assistant Adjutant-Gen.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
